INTRO: Read through this document to understand what is
needed to generate plots


###################################################
#                 DEPENDANCIES                    #
###################################################

Need access to newest of the following files:
MyBand.{cxx,h}
MyCrossSection.{cxx,h}
MyData.{cxx,h}
MyEvent.{cxx,h}
MyFrame.{cxx,h}
MyFrameData.{cxx,h}
MyGrids/
MyPDF/
MyPDF.{cxx,h}

Need access to te PDF sets, currently located:

  /afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/external/MCGenerators/lhapdf/5.8.8/share/lhapdf/PDFsets

Need access to SHERPA output, currently called sherpa21inputs and located:

  /afs/cern.ch/user/c/cembree/public/workspace/MyAnalysis/sherpatop21inputs

Also uses steering file to run, an example here:

  /afs/cern.ch/user/c/cembree/public/workspace/MyAnalysis/atlas2012_top.txt

Most of these dependancies are taken care of in 
the following setup process but you must change 
the setup based on your enevrionment.


###################################################
#                    SETUP                        #
###################################################
Perform the following:

  source setup.sh
  make

To prepare the envrionment you source the setupfile
called '$MYHOME/setuplxplus.sh'. After global envrion
-ment is setup, then we source the local 'setup.sh'
script and compile with 'make'.

The origonal sourcing of '$MYHOME/setuplxplus.sh' is 
done in my '.bashrc', so I only ever need to run my
local source of 'setup.sh'.

You can find an example STEERING file in this 
directory called 'STEERING_OUTLINE.txt' as well as
examples in: 
STEERING_EXAMPLE1.txt
STEERING_EXAMPLE2.txt 


###################################################
#                   RUNNING                       #
###################################################
Executable 'plot' takes 1 parameter:
1 - steering file

A steering file should emulate what can be found 
in the example steering file called 
'STEERING_EXAMPLE.txt', found at:

  /afs/cern.ch/user/c/cembree/public/workspace/MyAnalysis/STEERING_EXAMPLE.txt

An outline for a generic steering file including
all optional options is called 'STEERING_OUTLINE.txt'
and can be found at:

  /afs/cern.ch/user/c/cembree/public/workspace/MyAnalysis/STEERING_OUTLINE.txt


Output from running will show  in root, so you will 
need X11 forwarding if you are sshing in, which looks
something like:

  ssh -X username@lxplus.cern.ch


###################################################
#                EXAMPLE RUNS                     #
###################################################
EXAMPLE RUN(S):

EXPLAIN THIS RUN:

  ./plot atlas2012_top.txt

EXPLAIN THIS RUN:

  ./plot STEERING_EXAMPLE.txt

